channel.title: Incomplete caches?
channel.description: Im just curious to know why we have incomplete caches. I doubt Jagex gave us 50% (as an example) of their cache back in the day, what happens to those other files?

item.title: Incomplete caches?
item.dc:creator: @Advocatus Advocatus
item.description:
@Advocatus wrote:

[quote=“Tutorial, post:9, topic:542724”][quote author=RiiPiiNFtW link=topic=661600.msg4422210#msg4422210 date=1399005679]

Client saves bandwidth by only loading what needs to be loaded.

Really? I thought that they give you the full cache… sounds like a reasonable explanation though, thank you
[/quote]No, you’re used to the shitty cache downloaders now-a-days. Although, JAGGRAB/OnDemand servers are getting bigger finally now that there are tutorials and released. haha.

Does anyone know when JAGGRAB was first designed?[/quote]
Jaggrab was used in the rs2 beta client. So that would have been around 2003. I have no idea if it was used in rsc.
